File: Technicians analyse PCR samples amid the COVID-19 pandemic. AFP/Yamil Lage JOHANNESBURG - South Africa has recorded the highest number of daily COVID-19 infections since January. In the last 24-hours, over 13,200 people have tested positive. READ: COVID-19 | NICD says SA technically in third wave More than 7,800 of them are in Gauteng. The Western Cape has breached the one thousand mark with over 1,400 people infected with COVID-19. 136 people have lost their lives to the virus.